data.name: label96.Text
data.value: Jog direction and speed is set using Setpoint velocity 1 and 2. Setpoint velocity 1 is Jog 1 maximum speed and Setpoint velocity 2 is Jog 2 maximum speed. The direction of motion is set using negative values. in the library function EposControl the manual speed used is a percentage of these values.

data.name: label111.Text
data.value: The accuracy of the axis positioning is dependent on the accuracy of the "Drive / Load wheel circumference". To aid in this it is advised to drive the load a set distance, ie. 1000mm and then measure the actual distance the load has physically moved. The Physical start and Drive start position should be the same, use PLC position and servo position above.

data.name: label99.Text
data.value: Values to be used in the PLC parameter Data BlockIn the PLC program use only the physical values, for example if you want to move to position 1250mm at a speed of 100mm/min then setPOSITION = 1250.0 AND SETPSPEED = 100.0
